<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1574,2026]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">
Valves broadly elliptic-lanceolate with clearly convex margins and protracted, rostrate ends. Valve dimensions (n = 25): length 
<quantity box="[359,460,1613,1639]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="37.0" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="32.0">32–42 µ</quantity>
m, width 
<quantity box="[584,746,1613,1639]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.13" metricValueMin="0.97" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="11.3" valueMin="9.7">9.7–11.3 µm</quantity>
. Axial area linear to linear-lanceolate, narrow, slightly widening towards the central area. Central area a large, bow-tie-shaped fascia. Raphe filiform with weakly curved branches. Central raphe endings deflected to the secondary side with large, almost triangular-shaped, central pores. Terminal fissures bent to one side, opposite to the central endings. Striae geniculate, radiate near the centre, becoming convergent near the valve ends, 
<quantity box="[780,882,1768,1794]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="3.302" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[890,970,1768,1794]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
. Longitudinal lines absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="28" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1574,2026]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,333,1806,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Habitat:—</emphasis>
The species is rather rare on Livingston Island. On Hurd Peninsula, it was found relatively abundantly in only one sample taken from a 
<taxonomicName box="[713,1060,1845,1870]" class="Bryopsida" family="Amblystegiaceae" genus="Sanionia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="georgico-uncinata">
<emphasis box="[713,1060,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">Sanionia georgico-uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vegetation, growing around a periodically drying shallow brook close to the sea. On Byers Peninsula, the species was more common. The largest population was found on wet soil close to the sea with a clear presence of elephant seal input (Van de Vijver, pers. obs.). The species seems to prefer more aerial circumstances influenced by biogenic input such as penguin rookeries and elephant seal wallows (
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Vijver, B. &amp; Frenot, Y. &amp; Beyens, L." box="[690,990,2000,2026]" pageId="17" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 412" refId="ref17273" refString="Van de Vijver, B., Frenot, Y. &amp; Beyens, L. (2002) Freshwater diatoms from Ile de la Possession (Crozet archipelago, Subantarctica). Bibliotheca Diatomologica 46: 1 - 412." type="journal article" year="2002">
Van de Vijver 
<emphasis box="[861,919,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,1086]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,403,151,177]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Observations:—</emphasis>
There is much confusion about the correct taxonomic identity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cleve-Euler" authorityYear="1948" baseAuthorityName="Carlson" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="austroshetlandica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Pinnularia austroshetlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 1954, Manguin (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bourrelly, P. &amp; Manguin, E." box="[639,966,189,215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="7 - 58" refId="ref14596" refString="Bourrelly, P. &amp; Manguin, E. (1954) Contribution a la flore algale des Iles Kerguelen. Memoires de l'Institut Scientifique de Madagascar, series B 5: 7 - 58." type="journal article" year="1954">Bourrelly &amp; Manguin 1954</bibRefCitation>
) described a new species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1308,1436,190,215]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1308,1436,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Pinnularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
he named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molder" authorityYear="1952" box="[272,372,228,253]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="kolbei">
<emphasis box="[272,372,228,253]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. kolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molder" authorityYear="1952" box="[512,583,228,253]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="kolbei">
<emphasis box="[512,583,228,253]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">kolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had already been used by Mölder (1952: 27; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Fukushima, H. &amp; Ko-Bayashi, T. &amp; Yoshitake S." pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="107 - 113" refId="ref15128" refString="Fukushima, H., Ko-Bayashi, T. &amp; Yoshitake S. (2001) New diatom taxa from New island (Falkland Islands). In: A. Economou-Amilli, ed.) Proceedings of the 16 th International Diatom Symposium, 25 Aug. - 1 Sept. 2000, Athens &amp; Aegean Islands, 107 - 113." type="proceedings paper" year="2001">
Fukushima 
<emphasis box="[1302,1362,228,253]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2001: 107
</bibRefCitation>
) making a new name for Manguin’s species necessary; Fukushima 
<emphasis box="[1066,1131,265,290]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
proposed 
<taxonomicName authority="Fukushima, Ko-Bayashi &amp; Yoshitake" authorityName="Fukushima, Ko-Bayashi &amp; Yoshitake" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="parakolbei">
<emphasis box="[1266,1436,265,290]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. parakolbei</emphasis>
Fukushima, Ko-Bayashi &amp; Yoshitake
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fukushima, H. &amp; Ko-Bayashi, T. &amp; Yoshitake S." box="[651,1012,303,329]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="107 - 113" refId="ref15128" refString="Fukushima, H., Ko-Bayashi, T. &amp; Yoshitake S. (2001) New diatom taxa from New island (Falkland Islands). In: A. Economou-Amilli, ed.) Proceedings of the 16 th International Diatom Symposium, 25 Aug. - 1 Sept. 2000, Athens &amp; Aegean Islands, 107 - 113." type="proceedings paper" year="2001">
Fukushima 
<emphasis box="[805,871,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2001: 108
</bibRefCitation>
) as a substitute name. However, populations observed from the 
<collectingCountry box="[516,709,341,367]" name="Falkland Islands" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Falkland Islands</collectingCountry>
did not entirely conform to Manguin’s original description as they lacked the typical rostrate apices, a feature clearly stated (‘ 
<emphasis box="[890,1243,379,404]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">étirées rostrées aux extrémités</emphasis>
’) and illustrated by Manguin (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bourrelly, P. &amp; Manguin, E." box="[346,679,417,443]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="7 - 58" refId="ref14596" refString="Bourrelly, P. &amp; Manguin, E. (1954) Contribution a la flore algale des Iles Kerguelen. Memoires de l'Institut Scientifique de Madagascar, series B 5: 7 - 58." type="journal article" year="1954">Bourrelly &amp; Manguin 1954</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 52). 
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Vijver, B. &amp; Frenot, Y. &amp; Beyens, L." box="[796,1117,417,443]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 412" refId="ref17273" refString="Van de Vijver, B., Frenot, Y. &amp; Beyens, L. (2002) Freshwater diatoms from Ile de la Possession (Crozet archipelago, Subantarctica). Bibliotheca Diatomologica 46: 1 - 412." type="journal article" year="2002">
Van de Vijver 
<emphasis box="[970,1030,417,442]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
(2002)
</bibRefCitation>
separated the non-rostrate forms from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molder" authorityYear="1952" box="[290,389,455,480]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="kolbei">
<emphasis box="[290,389,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P.kolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
identifying them as 
<taxonomicName box="[628,753,455,480]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="bottnica">
<emphasis box="[628,753,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. bottnica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of 
<typeStatus box="[955,1005,455,481]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molder" authorityYear="1952" box="[1146,1246,455,480]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="kolbei">
<emphasis box="[1146,1246,455,480]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. kolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Van de Vijver, unpubl. res., slide number AD9087). both rostrate and non-rostrate specimens present in the same population; no other morphological or biometrical differences could be found. Additionally, detailed analysis of some large populations from other southern Indian Ocean islands yielded the same result (Van de Vijver, unpubl. res.). Therefore, it can be concluded that the 
<taxonomicName box="[683,808,606,631]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="bottnica">
<emphasis box="[683,808,606,631]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. bottnica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations of Ile de la Possession (
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Vijver, B. &amp; Frenot, Y. &amp; Beyens, L." pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 412" refId="ref17273" refString="Van de Vijver, B., Frenot, Y. &amp; Beyens, L. (2002) Freshwater diatoms from Ile de la Possession (Crozet archipelago, Subantarctica). Bibliotheca Diatomologica 46: 1 - 412." type="journal article" year="2002">
Van de Vijver 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
) and the 
<taxonomicName box="[359,516,644,669]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="parakolbei">
<emphasis box="[359,516,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. parakolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
population from the 
<collectingCountry box="[766,959,644,670]" name="Falkland Islands" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Falkland Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fukushima, H. &amp; Ko-Bayashi, T. &amp; Yoshitake S." box="[975,1242,644,670]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="107 - 113" refId="ref15128" refString="Fukushima, H., Ko-Bayashi, T. &amp; Yoshitake S. (2001) New diatom taxa from New island (Falkland Islands). In: A. Economou-Amilli, ed.) Proceedings of the 16 th International Diatom Symposium, 25 Aug. - 1 Sept. 2000, Athens &amp; Aegean Islands, 107 - 113." type="proceedings paper" year="2001">
Fukushima 
<emphasis box="[1115,1174,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
) are conspecific and the name 
<taxonomicName box="[314,441,682,707]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="parakolbei">
<emphasis box="[314,441,682,707]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">parakolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be used for both the rostrate and the non-rostrate specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,1086]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation author="Fukushima, H. &amp; Ko-Bayashi, T. &amp; Yoshitake S." box="[198,477,720,746]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="107 - 113" refId="ref15128" refString="Fukushima, H., Ko-Bayashi, T. &amp; Yoshitake S. (2001) New diatom taxa from New island (Falkland Islands). In: A. Economou-Amilli, ed.) Proceedings of the 16 th International Diatom Symposium, 25 Aug. - 1 Sept. 2000, Athens &amp; Aegean Islands, 107 - 113." type="proceedings paper" year="2001">
Fukushima 
<emphasis box="[335,393,720,745]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cleve-Euler" authorityYear="1948" baseAuthorityName="Carlson" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[618,961,720,745]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="austroshetlandica">
<emphasis box="[618,961,720,745]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Pinnularia austroshetlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be similar to but distinct enough from 
<taxonomicName box="[151,307,758,783]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="parakolbei">
<emphasis box="[151,307,758,783]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. parakolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
since the strongly protruding ends and the almost straight raphe distinguished the former. 
<typeStatus box="[1378,1436,757,783]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carlson" authorityYear="1913" box="[294,631,796,821]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Navicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="austroshetlandica">
<emphasis box="[294,631,796,821]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Navicula austroshetlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the basionym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cleve-Euler" authorityYear="1948" baseAuthorityName="Carlson" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[857,1216,796,821]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="austroshetlandica">
<emphasis box="[857,1216,796,821]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Pinnularia austroshetlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) has not yet been located. A careful examination of the description and drawing in 
<bibRefCitation author="Carlson, G. W. F." box="[951,1134,833,859]" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 94" refId="ref14664" refString="Carlson, G. W. F. (1913) Susswasseralgen aus der Antarktis, Sudgeorgien und den Falkland Inseln. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Schwedischen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903, unter Leitung von Dr. Otto Nordenskjold, Band 4 (Botanik): 1 - 94." type="book chapter" year="1913">Carlson (1913)</bibRefCitation>
and its comparison with specimens from different 
<taxonomicName box="[460,589,871,896]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="parakolbei">
<emphasis box="[460,589,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">parakolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-populations from the entire (sub-)Antarctic Region did not reveal any significant differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cleve-Euler" authorityYear="1948" baseAuthorityName="Carlson" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[555,811,909,934]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="austroshetlandica">
<emphasis box="[555,811,909,934]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. austroshetlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[875,1042,909,934]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="parakolbei">
<emphasis box="[875,1042,909,934]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. parakolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cleve-Euler" authorityYear="1948" baseAuthorityName="Carlson" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1140,1396,909,934]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="austroshetlandica">
<emphasis box="[1140,1396,909,934]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. austroshetlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="parakolbei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. parakolbei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Manguin" authorityName="Manguin" box="[337,627,947,973]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="kolbei">
<emphasis box="[337,439,947,972]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. kolbei</emphasis>
sensu Manguin
</taxonomicName>
are considered synonyms and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cleve-Euler" authorityYear="1948" baseAuthorityName="Carlson" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[994,1234,947,972]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="austroshetlandica">
<emphasis box="[994,1234,947,972]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. austroshetlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should therefore be given priority. Another name that may need adding is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peragallo" authorityYear="1921" box="[817,1027,985,1010]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Navicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="nivorum">
<emphasis box="[817,1027,985,1010]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">Navicula nivorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peragallo" authorityYear="1921" box="[1120,1311,985,1011]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Navicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="variety" species="nivorum" variety="elongata">
variety 
<emphasis box="[1208,1311,985,1010]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although the original material is apparently no longer available, the descriptions and drawings match clearly 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cleve-Euler" authorityYear="1948" baseAuthorityName="Carlson" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Pinnularia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="18" pageNumber="29" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="austroshetlandica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="29">P. austroshetlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
